Users are interested in being able to post template comment replies to issues, particularly when using JIRA for support. Atlassian support has configured scripts that use the Firefox GreaseMonkey plugin to present a row of drop-downs above the comment field, containing commonly used, pre-written answers by category.

Please create a page called something like 'Create drop-down template replies for JIRA comment fields' in the JIRA community space that makes these scripts available as unsupported downloads with brief setup instructions. The page should explain what these scripts do without being too specific to support, since they have other applications.

This page should be linked from the 'See Also' of http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/JIRA+as+a+support+system

