I want to search for issues that are assigned to any individuals in a particular group.  JIRA apparently distinguishes between a group name entered as *MGR: Smith* vs. *Mgr: Smith*, or *mgr: smith*.  Is it necessary to make this field case sensitive?  It creates a hardship, as various managers will be entering their own group name as search criteria, and I'm bound to get all kinds of calls if they do not use the precise case.  (I am aware that the group picker would eliminate this problem, but I prefer not to open up the list of groups to all managers).

When a project's fix-for version, Affects version and components are hidden in the field configuration, users visiting the the "Browse" project page see this cryptic message:

{quote}Note: The 'Project Information' panel is not available.{quote}

and have no idea what it means.

I raised an issue about this three years ago (JRA-5304). Since then numerous people have been confused by this (JRA-8913, JRA-5293, JSP-513 and most recently JSP-16616).

If we don't have time to fix it properly (JRA-5304) can we at least just improve the wording? Something like:

{quote}Note: No project information panels are available, as this project's version and component fields are disabled.{quote}

From a SAC case:

We'd like to have Greek Lucene indexing support added into JIRA. We've done a core modification for one of our customers, but we would really like to see it in the official codeline.

Objects affected:
* {{jira/src/etc/languages/default/com/atlassian/jira/web/action/JiraWebActionSupport.properties}}
{code}
admin.jira.allowed.language.greek=Greek
{code}

